article.headline: Longwood 85, S. Dakota 82
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Durann Neil hit a 3-pointer with 4 seconds left as Longwood defeated South Dakota 85-82 Thursday night, ending the Coyotes' five-game winning streak. Aaron Mitchell had 23 points for the Lancers (6-13), who also got 14 points and 15 rebounds from Antwan Carter. Charlie Westbrook, who had 14 points, gave South Dakota a 54-48 lead when he hit a jumper with 14:56 left. But the Lancers went on a 28-14 run over the next eight minutes to lead 76-68. South Dakota, which was led by Jake Thomas' 28 points, rallied to tie twice. The final tie came on a layup by Louie Krogman, who had 11 points, with 25 seconds left. Longwood called time and worked the ball to Neil for his game-winning shot. Neil had eight points. South Dakota failed to get off a tying attempt, as Longwood's Martiz Washington stole the ball from Thomas at the end.
